WEBVTT

00:07.891 --> 00:09.017
Wow, what's all this?

00:09.159 --> 00:11.923
Oh, I'm doing all the costumes
for Cooper's play.

00:16.032 --> 00:17.363
What?

00:17.500 --> 00:21.402
Nothing, nothing. I think you look real cute
with your needle and thread.

00:22.005 --> 00:24.337
Like my grandmother darning a sock.

00:27.243 --> 00:30.770
- Okay, just joking.
- Not funny.

00:32.148 --> 00:34.446
So any big plans today, birthday girl?

00:34.584 --> 00:35.642
Thought I forgot?

00:37.153 --> 00:39.121
No. You know me, Luc.

00:39.255 --> 00:42.622
I don't really like to make a big deal
about my birthday. Just let it go.

00:42.759 --> 00:45.751
Yeah, but this one is the big one, okay?

00:47.664 --> 00:49.598
Yeah, so let me at least take you out
to dinner.

00:50.633 --> 00:54.296
Okay. You know,
I've really gotta finish all these costumes.

00:54.437 --> 00:56.997
- I've got this headdress I've gotta do...
- Wait.

00:58.875 --> 01:01.537
I set it up. Please.
You have to come with me.

01:01.678 --> 01:03.839
It's just you and I.
It's great food, great wine.

01:03.980 --> 01:05.447
Please, it's important to me.

01:05.749 --> 01:08.411
- Just the two of us.
- Just the two of us.

01:08.985 --> 01:12.284
- Yeah.
- Okay, yes, yes, yes.

01:18.061 --> 01:19.892
- Hi, Kevin.
- Do you wanna call Sarah

01:20.029 --> 01:22.361
and sing "Happy Birthday" in a round?
It really annoys her.

01:24.000 --> 01:25.490
- How bored are you?
- Very.

01:25.635 --> 01:27.933
Why doesn't this woman
have a real coffee maker?

01:28.071 --> 01:30.403
- What woman?
- The woman I rented this house from.

01:30.540 --> 01:33.737
What's her name? Here you go.
"Leslie Culpepper."

01:33.877 --> 01:36.505
So how is it up in Ojai?
Have you found yourself yet?

01:37.814 --> 01:39.805
Well, not exactly.

01:39.949 --> 01:45.012
But I have discovered that peace and quiet
is actually very quiet and peaceful.

01:45.155 --> 01:48.955
- As long as your siblings don't call.
- Oh, what? Country life, you like it?

01:49.092 --> 01:52.528
Don't tell me you're getting
all <i>Little House on the Prairie</i> on us.

01:52.662 --> 01:53.856
<i>You know, I am.</i>

01:53.997 --> 01:56.397
I'll gonna start churning butter
before you know it

01:56.533 --> 01:59.400
and I'm gonna grow one of those
crazy long ponytails down my back

01:59.536 --> 02:01.128
or maybe a bun.

02:01.271 --> 02:03.466
Are we singing or not?

02:10.780 --> 02:12.372
Hello?

02:12.515 --> 02:14.642
Stop that right there.
The only thing more annoying

02:14.784 --> 02:17.446
than listening to you sing
is if Kevin joins in a round.

02:17.587 --> 02:18.849
Hi, Sarah.

02:19.622 --> 02:20.680
- Hi, Kevin.
- Hey.

02:20.824 --> 02:23.520
So, Sarah, how does it feel
to be the older sister?

02:23.660 --> 02:25.525
Oh, good, good.
You know, it's good, it's good.

02:25.662 --> 02:26.856
It's like any other year.

02:26.996 --> 02:29.021
I can't believe how old we're getting.
So depressed.

02:29.165 --> 02:32.931
Yeah. So, Kitty, how is it going
up in Ojai? Sorry.

02:33.069 --> 02:36.505
<i>You know, I actually think I like it.</i>
<i>I mean, it's very simple. It's very simple.</i>

02:36.639 --> 02:38.573
<i>People cook, people garden.</i>

02:38.708 --> 02:40.437
- <i>Do you have to go?</i>
- Nobody recognizes me.

02:40.577 --> 02:41.737
I could be anybody.

02:41.878 --> 02:45.211
It's like that summer at camp
I told everyone I was a teenage spy.

02:45.348 --> 02:46.838
<i>Oh, my God, soufflé.</i>

02:47.917 --> 02:49.782
I've always wanted to make soufflé.

02:49.919 --> 02:52.251
<i>I swear to you this time</i>
<i>I'm gonna learn how to cook.</i>

02:52.388 --> 02:54.083
See you tonight.

02:57.026 --> 02:59.051
Okay, listen. Here's the deal.

02:59.195 --> 03:04.758
No one is gonna talk anymore
about my birthday.

03:04.901 --> 03:06.061
- <i>Okay?</i>
- Why?

03:06.202 --> 03:10.798
There'll be no presents, no flowers
and absolutely no cake with candles.

03:10.940 --> 03:13.568
- What are you talking about?
- I'm just not into it this year.

03:14.010 --> 03:15.739
That's gonna be really hard, Sarah,

03:15.879 --> 03:18.541
because Luc is planning a surprise dinner
for you.

03:19.582 --> 03:22.380
No, he's not. No. No.
We're just going out.

03:22.518 --> 03:24.577
Just the two of us, very low-key.

03:24.721 --> 03:27.155
Wrong. It's at the restaurant.
We're all invited.

03:27.290 --> 03:29.485
I'm sorry, Sarah.
I know how you hate surprises.

03:29.626 --> 03:33.027
Okay, listen, you've got to call him. Kitty,
call and tell him that you can't make it.

03:33.162 --> 03:35.255
You live up in Ojai.
It's a really good excuse.

03:35.398 --> 03:37.696
- What's my excuse? I live upstairs.
- <i>I don't know.</i>

03:37.834 --> 03:40.769
You've got to wash your hair.
Kevin, I don't care. You're not going.

03:41.070 --> 03:43.129
Wait a minute.
You really don't want me to come?

03:43.273 --> 03:44.467
- No.
- Come on, it'll be fun.

03:44.607 --> 03:48.805
- Remember your 40th? I was so drunk.
- Yes, I do. That's the problem.

03:48.945 --> 03:50.344
Well, why is it a problem?

03:51.114 --> 03:55.050
Because Luc thinks
today is my 40th birthday.

03:55.184 --> 03:57.345
Sarah. I'm impressed.

03:57.487 --> 04:01.651
Oh, my God, you've been lying
about your age all this time?

04:01.791 --> 04:04.783
Yes. So just... You have to keep
your mouth shut. The two of you, okay?

04:04.928 --> 04:07.419
Good luck with that.
Because at some point, sooner or later...

04:07.563 --> 04:09.793
- <i>Oh, my God! No, no, no.</i>
- Kitty, are you all right?

04:09.933 --> 04:12.163
You know what? Everything's fine.
Everything's fine.

04:12.302 --> 04:14.202
It's just a little plumbing issue.

04:14.337 --> 04:15.998
No, no. See, you didn't do this right.

04:16.139 --> 04:18.971
You just hit tab.
And it automatically adds it for you.

04:19.108 --> 04:20.404
- Oh, okay. Sorry.
- Yeah.

04:20.543 --> 04:22.602
I know back in the day
they did things differently,

04:22.745 --> 04:24.440
but this is the 21st century, Nora.

04:24.580 --> 04:26.810
You can throw out your abacus.

04:26.950 --> 04:33.219
Yeah. I'll just do that.
Throw out my abacus.

04:33.356 --> 04:35.620
Oh, sorry.

04:36.125 --> 04:37.717
Okay.

04:39.195 --> 04:40.890
Well, that was snarky.

04:41.030 --> 04:43.498
Yes. Can I help...

04:43.933 --> 04:45.332
- Celia?
- Hi, Nora.

04:45.468 --> 04:48.369
Oh, my goodness. Celia, I almost
didn't recognize... You look fabulous.

04:48.504 --> 04:50.563
Oh, thank you.
What are you doing here?

04:50.707 --> 04:54.006
I'm just trying to reinvent myself.

04:54.143 --> 04:55.838
Me and my abacus.

04:55.979 --> 05:01.076
Oh, sweetie, there are easier ways
to reinvent yourself, you know?

05:01.284 --> 05:03.809
My son-in-law. He's a genius.

05:04.887 --> 05:08.084
- "Dr. Howard Brentley."
- Yeah, a real artist. I'm telling you.

05:11.594 --> 05:13.994
Celia. Oh, my gosh.

05:14.731 --> 05:16.358
Well, you look amazing.

05:16.499 --> 05:18.899
I was losing listings to all the younger,
prettier girls

05:19.035 --> 05:21.435
and I thought if I wanna compete
in the work force,

05:21.571 --> 05:24.904
then what goes up, you know,
must stay up.

05:25.041 --> 05:27.874
- I never would've known.
- It's like I just woke up from a long nap.

05:28.011 --> 05:29.103
Or a coma.

05:29.612 --> 05:32.547
And my boobs. I mean, they're back up
where I can actually see them again.

05:32.682 --> 05:34.445
They're up
where everyone can see them.

05:35.485 --> 05:37.885
- Oh, and look.
- You got your hands done?

05:38.021 --> 05:42.481
No, silly.
I'm engaged to a really wonderful man.

05:42.625 --> 05:43.785
We met on a cruise.

05:43.926 --> 05:46.520
I mean, he's six years younger than I am,
but who's counting?

05:48.798 --> 05:52.928
- So your whole life changed just like that.
- Yeah. I mean, it's out-patient surgery.

05:53.069 --> 05:55.936
A couple weeks on the couch,
popping pills, watching <i>General Hospital,</i>

05:56.072 --> 05:58.666
and, poof, it's like magic.

05:59.876 --> 06:01.901
You want me to see
if I can get the good doctor

06:02.045 --> 06:03.706
to squeeze you in for a consultation?

06:04.680 --> 06:06.671
Well, I...

06:07.617 --> 06:09.710
- Well...
- Nora, everyone's doing it.

06:09.852 --> 06:10.978
- They are?
- Oh, yeah.

06:11.821 --> 06:15.882
Take back your power, honey.
You won't regret it.

06:17.860 --> 06:20.727
- Rebecca? Rebecca?
- Dad. Hey.

06:20.863 --> 06:22.626
Hold on one second.
No, they want an overview

06:22.765 --> 06:24.790
at the meeting,
so I need those shipping reports.

06:24.934 --> 06:27.869
Okay? Yeah, no, I gotta go.
Okay, thanks.

06:28.004 --> 06:29.494
- Hi.
- Hi.

06:30.807 --> 06:32.468
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah.

06:32.608 --> 06:35.236
- Actually, it's better than okay.
- Here. Sit down.

06:35.611 --> 06:38.808
- Yeah? What's going on? How's Mom?
- Oh, she's getting better.

06:38.948 --> 06:41.280
You know, she's never going
to get all of her memory back,

06:41.417 --> 06:45.786
- but she's less frustrated now, so...
- Good.

06:45.922 --> 06:50.120
Listen, I can't make any promises,
but I think she's ready to see you.

06:50.993 --> 06:54.952
What? I mean,
last time she didn't even know who I was

06:55.098 --> 06:57.123
and she was so upset.
The doctors said...

06:57.266 --> 07:02.101
Well, I know what the doctor said,
but she's been asking about you a lot.

07:02.238 --> 07:03.330
- Really?
- Yeah.

07:03.739 --> 07:07.140
Yeah. She heard
some stories about you

07:07.276 --> 07:10.336
and for whatever reason
they seem to have gotten through.

07:10.480 --> 07:14.541
Yeah, I think she finally really grasps
that she has a daughter.

07:15.485 --> 07:17.578
Oh, my God.

07:17.787 --> 07:21.223
- So I can see her. Like, soon?
- How about tonight?

07:24.260 --> 07:27.093
So, what did you tell her?
What stories did you tell her?

07:27.230 --> 07:28.663
Actually, it wasn't me.

07:29.198 --> 07:32.895
- Who was it?
- It was Justin.

07:34.000 --> 07:40.074
